datasetName: RB - Rio de Janeiro Botanical Garden Herbarium Collection
name: Diandrolyra tatianae Soderstr. & Zuloaga
occurrenceRemarks: Rhizomatous grass with only one culm in flower; plant probably not in natural habitat.
fieldNotes: Steep forested slopes above mountain stream. Four years ago mountain slides here caused great devastation; so that undergrowth now consists of palm seedlings and small shrubs.

datasetName: RB - Rio de Janeiro Botanical Garden Herbarium Collection
name: Diandrolyra tatianae Soderstr. & Zuloaga
occurrenceRemarks: General flowering said to begin here in September. Common grass in vegetation between rocks next to stream in dense shade; mostly past flower with many young plants.
fieldNotes: Dense forest next to small rocky stream with fast current; vegetation with Pharus latifolius, Heliconia, ferns, Bromeliaceae, Arecaceae.
